<br>
The other night, someone was selling these bags, which were never intended to be sold I take it. They are awesome bags, and some people wanted to use this to make money.<br>
<br>
This upset some people that do have the ability to make the bags so they decided to make the bags and hand them out for free to anyone that wanted them.<br>
<br>
Some people were upset because they think that giving the bags away to anyone has runed the economy for people that want to sell them.<br>
<br>
Here is a quote from the other thread:<br>
~~<br>
To set the record straight, I was the one who initiated this 2.5 hour flooding of the masses with bags. I am Fhade, Quillestrae's husband. In /market this eve a poor buyer announced they received a bag similar to a tinkerer's bag in wt, stats, capacity and wt reduction for 300pp. Of course the entire channel corrected this person as there is no way such a bag would be found so cheap. After much debate the person was correct actually and to some folks had been the victim of a shady deal. The bags in question are quested. You summon a no rent bag (no drop on other servers) from a GM Trade Skill Trophy (also no drop elsewhere) then turn said free summoned bag into an NPC in bazaar named Jollum who in turn returns a LORE (no drop version on other servers) for the free bag. Now to myself and a few other Trophy holders this was just another of the ways to exploit the population for platinum for little or no work involved due to a No Drop loophole. <br>
<br>
My purpose in starting the mass flood of free bags upon the market was two fold. First, to prevent the unknowing from shelling out hard earned pp for an item thats effortless to get. Second to bring to light yet another loop hole in the NO DROP coding. Only a few fought this topic as not an issue, some (including myself) /petitioned /reported the issue, where far far more were just happy to get a nice item. There are a few No Drop loop holes folks have found but of those this was the only effortless one. The rest of them I can understand to a certain point due to factions, the length of travel time etc, but cannot accept them completely.<br>
<br>
The GM Trophy is a high trade skill item for those who don't know. We agree it takes much skill and much investment to attain such skills and thats what this and the lore bag were meant to reward. The fact that someone used a self only intended reward to further advance their pp stash for little effort outside of the trade skill is what set this whole thing off. Verant takes very little responsibility for what happens on FV. They never have the GM support nor the staffing to help fix many of the known No Drop issues let alone the dozens of other serious issues here. Tonight's issue was a big red flag to Verant since emails and petitions of one person do very little. Perhaps the flood got their attention. Just a note on our Trophy, we have one but neither of us could make it, we have no trade skills over 110. We got this in trades for other items. Its a commonly sold/traded thing here where other places its no drop. The whole &quot;You didn't deserve the trophy so you don't have the right to dictate how its used&quot; issue is garbage. I had at least 2 or 3 others with me who did earn their trophies in complete agreement with what I stood for and helped. /hugs to them. If they wish to join in the thread then I leave that to them.<br>
<br>
The only folks I see upset over this whole ordeal are ppl who didn't get a bag or who are mad at losing a free source of income. /rant off, to each his own I guess. I take full responsibility for my actions and any repercussions that follow but in my heart I did the right thing. Rarely does one have the opportunity, let alone the timing, to take actions for what they believe is honorable. I was truly humbled to see so many happy folks who understood why this was happening.<br>
<br>
Peace and Love all!<br>
<br>
Fhade<br>
Spiritual Healer of the North<br>
Fighting dishonor for 46 seasons <br>
<br>
~~<br>
I agree with the people that gave the bags away, and the next night i gave away over 60 bags myself to anyone that wanted one. <br>
<br>
The 60 some odd bags I gave away, they were gifts.<br>
<br>
I got a tell from someone tonight when I logged on, really mad at me, they were selling the bags for 1500pp each, and made over 9k so far. Funny thing is, this person didnt make the trophy himself through his tradeskill efforts, he bought the trophy for 15k.<br>
<br>
As of now, the Gnome is not there, I was told the gms removed him for now while its under investigation.<br>
I didnt realize this was a bug, just like many of the other no drop items on our server that make us unique.<br>
<br>
Thanks for hearing my 2 coppers,<br>
<br>
Phedre<br>
<br>
