<br>
To &quot;Fix&quot; this now would require so much mucking about the cure might be worse that the problem.  But I do agree that charging for the bags, at least charging more than a nominal tip, is unreasonable.  50 platinum, as for a port or for a rezz from a cleric who happened to be standing right there, I can see.<br>
<br>
Just remember folks, it isn't usefullness along that determines value.  Value is determined by scarcity.  And when there are dozens and dozens (possibly hundreds) of bag-producing factories out there that can make them for the click of a button, they will be dirt-cheap.  Basic economics.<br>
<br>
Kudos to people who flooded the market, and special kudos to those who went to the trouble of explaining what was really happening and why.  Knowledge is Power.<br>
